added.title: The Master
added.description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?

added.title: The Future
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Banana Joe investigate Banana Barbara's mysterious disappearance and uncover an old rival's shadowy scheme in the process.

added.title: The Factory
added.description: Gumball and Darwin follow Nicole to the Rainbow Factory for Bring your Kids to Work Day. They are expecting a magical place full of dreams and wonder but it turns out to be a little less magical than they'd hoped. Despite the fact nobody wants them there, they end up saving the factory from being closed down.

added.title: The Web
added.description: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online. In fact they are in serious need of the boys help with even the simplest of tasks. And no more so than their mom, Nicole.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Decisions
added.description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

added.title: The Best
added.description: No matter what Gumball does, Carmen thinks she knows better. Gumball attempts to gain the moral high ground but fails spectacularly.  He decides that self-improvement isn't his style. The only option he has left is to bring Carmen down to his level.

added.title: The Deal
added.description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

added.title: The Puppets
added.description: While searching the attic for items to put in their yard sale, Gumball and Darwin stumble upon a load of their old toys. Darwin is especially pleased when he finds his old puppets, Frank and Howdy. However, as Darwin starts playing with them again, Gumball gradually realizes that Frank and Howdy are actually playing with Darwin...

added.title: The List
added.description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: King of the Zombeez
added.description: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

added.title: Hiccup the Volume
added.description: Monkey Chunks has hiccups and Biblia Tick hires the Warriors to get rid of them.

added.title: Ghosthaste
added.description: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

added.title: Hangry Hangry Hoppus
added.description: The Warriors battle a monster version of Hoppus, the rabbit transformed by the Cursed Garlic Magisword.

added.title: Pachydermus Packard and the Camp of Fantasy
added.description: A doctor orders Mr. Pachydermus to have an adventure, so he attends the Warriors' super-annoying, "Fantasy Camp"!

added.title: Let's Team Up Because We Aren't Bad Friends
added.description: The Warriors fear that they've been ignoring their pals, so they team up with Witchy Simone and Noville for a BIG MISSION, only to discover that their friends aren't into it anymore.

added.title: She Wore Red Velvet
added.description: When Booster and the JLA come under attack by a mysterious and unrelenting new villainess known as Red Velvet, Booster comes to realize she's actually the fiance he left at the altar in the future.

added.title: Las Decisiones
added.description: Darwin finalmente se cansa de los consejos de Gumball y busca un nuevo mentor.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Red
added.description: Gumball y Darwin le dan a Nicole un curso intensivo de computación.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Corazon
added.description: El señor Robinson intenta recuperar la amistad de Gumball y Darwin y falla una y otra vez.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Las manecillas del tiempo
added.description: El maestro Wu intenta completar una batalla que comenzó hace décadas contra Acronix.

added.title: La incubacion
added.description: Los Ninja descubren un nuevo enemigo en medio de ellos.

added.title: Una epoca de traidores
added.description: Lloyd lucha con su papel como maestro en entrenamiento y Nya hace todo lo posible para reiniciar a Zane.

added.title: Carroneros
added.description: Lloyd se da cuenta de que hacerse cargo del debilitado Maestro Wu no es una tarea fácil.

added.title: Una linea en la arena
added.description: Jay lucha por defender la casa de su familia.

added.title: El ataque
added.description: Los Ninja celebran su escape.

added.title: Secretos revelados
added.description: Los secretos se revelan cuando Nya se enfrenta al impostor Samurai X, Kai persigue la verdad sobre sus padres y los otros Ninja buscan desesperadamente localizar y rescatar al Maestro Wu.

added.title: Pausa y efecto
added.description: Kai se enfrenta a su padre solo para descubrir que sus padres son en realidad cautivos. Mientras tanto, los Ninja trabajan para liberar a Wu, Cyrus Borg y otros cautivos.

added.title: Saltar del fuego a un mar hirviente
added.description: Kai y Nya son chantajeados para que usen sus poderes elementales combinados para salvar al Maestro Wu que se desvanece rápidamente.

added.title: Perdidos en el tiempo
added.description: Kai y Nya se escabullen en un intento desesperado por salvar al Maestro Wu.

added.title: El Amo
added.description: Los Watterson juegan un juego de rol fantástico para resolver sus diferencias.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: La mamá de Banana Joe puede predecir el futuro, pero no puede predecir su propia desaparición.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Fabrica
added.description: Gumball y Darwin salvan la Fábrica de Arcoíris.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Me Llamo Jose
added.description: Raven les da nuevos superpoderes a los Titanes, pero a ellos les cuesta adaptarse.

added.title: El Poder De Los Camarones
added.description: Aqualad usa camarones y carne de primera calidad para recuperar a Raven.

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: Genio Presidente
added.description: Robin elabora un plan para enriquecerse a base de monedas de un centavo, pero Starfire cree que las monedas son mágicas.

added.title: Mas dinero, Mas problemas
added.description: Los Titanes hacen que Robin les dé una vuelta por Wayne Manor y descubra lo divertido que es ser rico.

added.title: Unos y Ceros
added.description: Los Titanes construyen un robot con inteligencia artificial para que elabore una pizza que nunca antes fue hecha.

added.title: Concurso de Disfraces
added.description: Hartos de que los Hive Five les ganen en el concurso de disfraces, los Titanes elaboran un plan para ganar.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 1
added.description: Cuando su mundo comienza a desaparecer, los Titanes deben confrontar a sus creadores.

added.title: Episodio 200 Super Indulgente y Espectacular: Parte 2
added.description: Los Titanes descubren lo difícil que es producir dibujos animados cuando hacen uno sobre Michael y Aaron.

added.title: Chica Bestia
added.description: Mientras los Titanes se enfrentan a Madame Rouge, Chico Bestia está entusiasmado por conocer a Chica Bestia, su equivalente femenina.

added.title: Cambio de Temporada
added.description: Cuando nuestros héroes regresan de sus vacaciones, K.O. se horroriza al descubrir que las cosas cambiaron.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Lord Vaquero Darrell
added.description: Todos se ven obligados a enfrentar grandes cambios en Boxmore.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Festival de Cine en la Plaza
added.description: Cuando se organiza un festival de cine propio en la Plaza, iEnid y Rad están seguros de que su obra ganará!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Tu Mundo es una Ilusion
added.description: K.O. intenta ayudar a un héroe en problemas y termina necesitando ayuda él también.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Jethro Es Tuyo
added.description: iK.O. consigue su primera misión en solitario!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Hermanos Rivales
added.description: Cuando Raymond, un nuevo robot, derrota a los tres héroes para robarle el letrero a Gar, K.O. se alía a Darrell y a Shannon para recuperarlo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Presentando a Joe Kaffi
added.description: K.O. intenta ayudar a Joe Kaffi, su comediante favorito.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: TKO
added.description: Parte 1: En busca de poder, K.O. acepta la ayuda de una figura misteriosa./ Parte 2: Nuestros héroes se alían para salvar la Plaza de una nueva amenaza.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Dias de gloria
added.description: K.O. escribe un informe escolar sobre Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Broken Boogie
added.description: When the Boogie Man loses his mojo, Uncle Grandpa steps in to help.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: Tongue Tied
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a shy kid gain confidence.

added.title: Uncle Dummy
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve try to convince Mr. Gus that his ventriloquist dummy is alive.

added.title: G'day Mornin'
added.description: Uncle grandpa goes to Australia where he must stop an out-of-control collecting kangaroo before he destroys the Earth.

added.title: Fear of Flying
added.description: Uncle grandpa helps a young boy overcome his fear of flying.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Mustache Tree
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa runs out of mustaches, he travels to the mustache tree to stock up. But upon arrival, it seems a new clan of elves have become very territorial over the tree. Now, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must fight in order to obtain a new 'stache.

added.title: Wasteland
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa neglects his garbage duties, he embarks on a quest to save his friends from the overflowing pile of trash.

added.title: Duck Lips
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa molds her mouth into duck lips, a young girl must face the consequences of her new found popularity.

removed.title: Cuttin' Corners
removed.description: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake… But are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

removed.title: The Joy
removed.description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

removed.title: The Move
removed.description: Clayton is a compulsive liar, but Gumball discovers he wasn't lying about his awesome martial arts move. Gumball confronts Clayton about his fabled Seven Pressure Point Heart Exploding Technique, assuming it's another one of his outlandish claims. Darwin and Gumball intervene to help Clayton start embracing the truth. However, when they discover the move is as effective as he claimed, they really wish he'd been lying.

removed.title: The Inquisition
removed.description: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways. But who wants to be normal? Certainly not Gumball and Darwin.

removed.title: The Robot
removed.description: Gumball discovers that Bobert is planning to take over his identity and replace him!

removed.title: The Cringe
removed.description: When the uncomfortableness between them reaches new levels, Gumball and Hot Dog Guy decide they have to confront their ongoing awkwardness by making things as awkward as possible.

removed.title: The Law
removed.description: Donut Cop shows Gumball and Darwin that the smallest misdemeanour can lead to a breakdown in law.  Gumball jaywalks and is pulled over by Donut Cop. When Gumball objects he is told that even the smallest misdemeanor can lead to a breakdown in law. In an effort to impress the kids Donut Cop takes them for a ride-along in his cop car and gets carried away, progressively breaking the law himself. He soon proves that the tiniest offense can indeed snowball into complete lawlessness!

removed.title: The Rival
removed.description: The Wattersons look back on Anais' first days in the Watterson house. Gumball and Darwin quickly find themselves up an opponent who is able to outsmart them at every turn.

removed.title: The BFFS
removed.description: Gumball's old BFF Fuzzy, turns up on his doorstep. Darwin struggles to accept that there was someone before him and fails to contain his jealousy. But is Darwin right to mistrust Fuzzy? Does Fuzzy actually have sinister motives for reconnecting with his old BFF?

removed.title: The One
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin are joking around, but when Tobias joins in and makes fun of Gumball, he's incredibly offended. They explain to Tobias that to make those jokes he'd need to be higher on Gumball's friend list. They think that's the end of it, but Tobias is after that number one spot.

removed.title: The Sucker
removed.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.
